==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[stol]]'', "seat", "throne". Confer Dutch ''[[stoel]]'', "chair", German ''[[Stuhl]]'', "chair", Old Norse ''[[stoll]]'', "chair", "seat", Gothic ''[[stols]]'', "throne".

===Noun===
'''stool''' ([[stools]])

# a [[seat]] for one person without a [[back]] or [[armrest]]
# a [[footstool]]
# [[fæces]], [[excrement]]. The word ''stool'' is preferred to ''[[fæces]]'' and ''[[excrement]]'' in medical use.
#(''archaic'') a [[decoy]]

====Derived terms====
*[[stool piegon]], [[stoolie]]

